Package lotus.domino

Interface Summary
ACL Represents the access control list (ACL) of a database.
ACLEntry Represents a single entry in an access control list.
AdministrationProcess Represents the administration process.
Agent Represents an agent.
AgentContext Represents the agent environment of the current program, if an agent is running it.
Base The Base class defines methods that are common to all the classes.
ColorObject Represents a color.
Database Represents a Notes database.
DateRange Represents a range of dates and times.
DateTime Represents a date and time.
DbDirectory Represents the Domino databases on a server or the local computer.
Document Represents a document in a database.
DocumentCollection Represents a collection of documents from a database, selected according to specific criteria.
DxlExporter Represents the conversion of Domino data to DXL (Domino XML).
DxlImporter Represents the conversion of DXL (Domino XML) to Domino data.
EmbeddedObject Represents any one of the following: An embedded object An object link A file attachment Note: Embedded objects and object links are not supported for OS/2, UNIX, and the Macintosh.
Form Represents a form in a database.
International Represents the international settings in the operating environment, for example, the Regional Settings in the Windows Control Panel.
Item Represents a discrete value or set of values in a document.
Log Enables you to record actions and errors that take place during a program's execution.
MIMEEntity Represents an item of type MIME (Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions).
MIMEHeader Represents a header in a MIME (Multipurpose Internet Mail Extensions) document.
Name Represents a user or server name.
Newsletter Document or set of documents that contains information from, or links to, several other documents.
NoteCollection Represents a collection of Domino design and data elements in a database.
NotesError  
Outline Represents an outline in a database.
OutlineEntry Represents an entry in an outline.
PVTConstants  
Registration Represents the creation or administration of an ID file.
Replication Represents the replication settings of a database.
ReplicationEntry Represents the replication settings for a pair of servers in a database.
RichTextDoclink Represents a doclink in a rich text item.
RichTextItem Represents an item of type rich text.
RichTextNavigator Represents a means of navigation in a rich text item.
RichTextParagraphStyle Represents rich text paragraph attributes.
RichTextRange Represents a range of elements in a rich text item.
RichTextSection Represents a collapsible section in a rich text item.
RichTextStyle Represents rich-text attributes.
RichTextTab Represents a tab in a rich text paragraph style.
RichTextTable Represents a table in a rich text item.
Session Is the root of the Domino Objects containment hierarchy, providing access to the other Domino objects, and represents the Domino environment of the current program.
Stream Represents a stream of binary or character data.
View Represents a view or folder of a database and provides access to documents within it.
ViewColumn Represents a column in a view or folder.
ViewEntry Represents a view entry.
ViewEntryCollection Represents a collection of view entries of type document sorted in view order.
ViewNavigator Represents a view navigator.
WebServiceHandler
